<P>
INSURER APPEALS POLICY RENEWAL ORDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Travelers group of insurance companies Friday asked the California Supreme 
Court to overturn an order issued last week by state Insurance Commissioner 
Roxani Gillespie requiring it to renew about 22,000 car insurance policies in 
California. 
</P>
<P>
Noting that four Travelers subsidiaries are seeking to withdraw from the auto 
insurance business in the state, Travelers Executive Vice President Thomas 
McAboy said the appeal contends that the company "has a basic constitutional 
right to cease doing private passenger automobile business in California," 
regardless of any provisions to the contrary in Proposition 103. During the 
appeal, Travelers has said it will renew all policies. 
</P>
