<HEADLINE>
<P>
DISPARITIES IN PROPERTY TAXES CREATED BY PROPOSITION 13 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Some of your readers defended the passage of Prop. 13 by starting that prior to 
July 1, 1978, there was doubt whether citizens had the right or the privilege 
to own property. This means that Prop. 13 gave everybody the "right" to 
ownership. Of course, this happened because someone else is being forced to 
pick up their share of property taxes. I wonder what would happen if these 
people, who cried out so loudly that taxes were making it impossible to own 
their own houses, had to fork over their fair share of taxes instead of forcing 
the rest of us to carry part of their burden? 
</P>
<P>
CHARLES D. WOODS 
</P>
<P>
Garden Grove 
</P>
