<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONTROVERSY OVER GUN CONTROL LAWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Of course, I don't enjoy the perspective of Davis on the gun control issue, but 
it does appear to me those favoring control have offered compromise over and 
over again only to meet with adamant opposition from the gun lobby and its 
friends in national and local legislatures. 
</P>
<P>
The truth is the National Rifle Assn. has mounted effective campaigns at every 
level to block attempts to regulate plastic guns, Teflon-coated ammunition, 
Saturday night specials, etc. 
</P>
<P>
Accusing anti-gun forces of "sitting like pigs in the middle of the road" is a 
cop out. The pun is intentional. 
</P>
<P>
LOUIS M. ST. MARTIN 
</P>
<P>
Pomona 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
