<HEADLINE>
<P>
USC MIGHT CONSIDER DROPPING BASKETBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
USC basketball has sunk to the absolute bottom, and no one seems to care. The 
fans, students and even the administration all apparently have long ago given 
up on the sport. Despite the dismal record this season, only the coach has 
questioned the coaching, and everyone seems content to let the team fade into 
oblivion. 
</P>
<P>
But the team's lack of success goes beyond coaching, poor talent and fan 
support. There has been something fundamentally wrong with the basketball 
program at USC for years. Maybe it's something as basic as not having a 
legitimate home arena, but if the school's attitude toward the sport is going 
to continue, USC should seriously consider dropping intercollegiate basketball 
and using the money elsewhere. 
</P>
<P>
WAYNE PETERS 
</P>
<P>
North Hollywood 
</P>
</TEXT>
