<P>
REBEL ROUSTERS MEET TONIGHT AT IRVINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBYN NORWOOD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Fullerton and UC Irvine, two teams that have upset Nevada Las Vegas 
in the past week, meet at 7:30 tonight at Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton and Irvine are the only Big West Conference teams that have beaten 
UNLV this season. Irvine beat UNLV, 99-98, last Saturday night. Fullerton 
pulled a 93-92 overtime upset Thursday night on Wayne Williams' three-point 
shot at the buzzer. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine (9-11, 6-5) won the first meeting with Fullerton this season, taking a 
77-73 victory Feb. 2, in a game in which center Ricky Butler scored a 
career-high 23 points. Since then, Butler has scored at least 20 points in two 
other Irvine victories. 
</P>
<P>
The Anteaters, who have won three games in a row, will be trying to put 
together a four-game winning streak for the first time since January, 1987. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton (10-10, 5-6) has won two straight since the loss to Irvine, upsetting 
UC Santa Barbara and UNLV. The Titans' Cedric Ceballos, a 6-foot-7 forward, is 
leading the Big West in scoring, averaging 21.5 points a game. ROBYN NORWOOD 
</P>
