<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles Times announced that Donald J. Maldonado, vice president of 
display advertising, has decided to take early retirement, effective March 1. 
He will continue to work for The Times as a consultant. Maldonado, 61, started 
with the paper in 1952 as a retail display advertising sales trainee. He became 
director of display advertising in 1969 and was named a vice president in June, 
1988. Frank O'Toole, 61, assistant director of display advertising, will become 
acting director of the department. 
</P>
</TEXT>
