<HEADLINE>
<P>
JUDY DAVIS SET TO STAR IN 'HAPGOOD' AT DOOLITTLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Australian actress Judy Davis has been set to star in the American premiere of 
Tom Stoppard's "Hapgood," an Ahmanson production to be presented at the 
Doolittle, April 12-July 9. 
</P>
<P>
Davis, who received a 1984 Academy Award nomination (Best Actress) for her role 
in David Lean's "A Passage to India," received a British Academy Award as best 
actress and best newcomer for her film debut in "My Brilliant Career" as well 
as numerous other awards from the Australian Film Institute and an Emmy for her 
portrayal of the young Golda Meir in "A Woman Called Golda." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA021189-0082 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 17161 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
February 11, 1989, Saturday, Home Edition 
</P>
