<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASKETBALL; 
</P>
<P>
EMPIRE LEAGUE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
EL DORADO WINS 14TH GAME IN ROW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DENNIS KAISER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
There was plenty of incentive for El Dorado and Cypress high schools Friday 
night in their Empire League boys' basketball finale. 
</P>
<P>
El Dorado, which already had clinched the league title, had an opportunity to 
close out the regular season with a 14-game winning streak and enter the 
Southern Section 3-A playoffs with a perfect league record. 
</P>
<P>
Cypress had a chance to avenge a defeat earlier in the season to El Dorado 
before heading into the 4-A playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
The Golden Hawks remained perfect in league play, 60-57. 
</P>
<P>
"Obviously we're playing well," El Dorado Coach Wayne Carlson. El Dorado is 
20-4 overall, 10-0 in league play, the first El Dorado team to go undefeated in 
league competition. 
</P>
<P>
Cypress (11-13, 6-4) and Los Alamitos tied for second in league play. 
</P>
<P>
It looked as if the Centurions might claim second place outright for nearly 
three quarters. They led, 19-18, lead on a Mark Johnson basket with 47 seconds 
remaining in the first quarter. Johnson led Cypress with 20 points. 
</P>
<P>
Cypress built an eight-point lead, 45-37, in the third. 
</P>
<P>
The Centurions held leading scorer and rebounder Matt Luke and starting guard 
Mike Renaud to three points each in the second and third quarters. 
</P>
<P>
But they couldn't contain either in the final quarter, when the Hawks outscored 
Cypress, 16-7, to escape with a victory. 
</P>
<P>
Renaud led the Hawks' balanced scoring attack with 15 points, including nine in 
the final 8 minutes. Luke finished with 12 points, 21 rebounds and four steals. 
</P>
<P>
The Hawks trailed, 50-46, going into the final quarter, but Luke sank two free 
throws and tipped in a Jerome Facione miss with 7:17 left to get the Hawks to 
within a basket at 50-48. 
</P>
<P>
In the final 4 minutes Luke had three steals, the second of which led to a 
Renaud basket at 2:57 that tied the score at 54-54. Another Luke steal with 
1:36 remaining led to two Renaud free throws and El Dorado's first lead of the 
game since the first quarter at 56-54. 
</P>
<P>
One of Luke's biggest rebounds came after a miss with 50 seconds to go by Jared 
Rice, who had 19 points. Mike Bradach was fouled and sank both shots for a 
58-54 lead. 
</P>
<P>
Katella 64, Los Alamitos 56 -- Brian Yourstone scored 25 points to lead the 
Knights (7-15, 3-7) at Katella. The Knights outscored the Griffins, 19-11, in 
the fourth quarter to pull away for the victory. Mike Wilson scored 17 points 
and Robert Conlisk 14 for Los Alamitos (11-14, 6-4), which enters the 5-A 
playoffs. 
</P>
