<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION BOYS' BASKETBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Harvard 78, Bell-Jeff 71 -- The Saracens, who trailed by as many as 10 points 
in the first half, outscored Bell-Jeff, 39-25, in the second half to notch a 
surprising San Fernando Valley League win at Harvard. Mike Beckwith scored a 
team-high 21 points and Rick Osterloh scored 10 of his 18 points in the fourth 
quarter for Harvard. 
</P>
<P>
Bell-Jeff guard Greg Dunn, who scored a game-high 26 points, was knocked 
unconscious in a fourth-quarter collision with Osterloh. Nick Sanderson scored 
24 for the Guards (19-4, 7-3), who dropped their second consecutive game. 
</P>
<P>
Notre Dame 71, Chaminade 68 -- Ken Hicks scored a game-high 27 points and Brian 
Jones added 19 to help the Knights to a San Fernando Valley League win at 
Chaminade. With Notre Dame trailing, 61-60, with about four minutes to play, 
the Knights (16-8, 10-0) received a two-shot technical foul when fans threw 
debris on the court. Brian Jones made both free throws and Notre Dame hung on 
to clinch an undefeated league season. 
</P>
<P>
Pete Miller (25 points), Chris Bruckner (14) and Charlie Fei (12) paced the 
Eagles (8-12, 3-7). 
</P>
<P>
Westlake 58, Channel Islands 49 -- Westlake converted 21 of 35 field-goal 
attempts (60%) against the host Raiders, who finished a winless Marmonte League 
season. Senior center Kurt Schwan scored a game-high 25 points and had 16 
rebounds to lead Westlake (15-9, 8-4), which placed third in league play. 
Schwan made 10 of 14 shots. 
</P>
<P>
Royal 82, Thousand Oaks 65 -- Royal (12-12, 7-5) must hope for an at-large 
playoff berth after finishing fourth in the Marmonte League. The host 
Highlanders built a 45-31 halftime lead, but Thousand Oaks (10-13, 5-7), led by 
Jeff Peterson (team-high 15 points), trimmed Royal's lead to eight late in the 
third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
J. P. Ouellette, however, made a three-point basket -- his 61st of the season 
-- to douse the Lancers' rally. Ouellette finished with a game-high 28 points. 
</P>
<P>
Burroughs 84, Burbank 67 -- Marnie Calderon scored 20 points and had eight 
assists and Dan Murphy added 18 points to lead the Indians (17-6, 9-1) in a 
Foothill League game at Burbank. 
</P>
<P>
Kahyeed Murray scored 14, and Paul Tapp and Edmundo Zepeda each scored 13 for 
Burbank (5-16, 4-6). 
</P>
<P>
Hart 86, Schurr 73 -- Hart (13-10, 7-3) captured second place in the Foothill 
League with the win at Schurr. Senior forward Brett Wilson scored a game-high 
27 points. Frank Butterfield (16 points, seven assists), Chad Fotheringham 
(11), Rob Curwen (10) scored in double figures for Hart. 
</P>
<P>
Saugus 56, Canyon 55 -- Aaron Volpe hit a three-point basket with four seconds 
left as Saugus snapped a 19-game losing streak in the Golden League game. 
Canyon led, 55-47, with two minutes left but failed to score thereafter. 
</P>
<P>
Trailing, 55-51, Saugus (2-20, 1-9) narrowed the deficit to two with 30 seconds 
left when John Harris scored after intercepting an inbounds pass. 
</P>
<P>
Sean Legaux (19 points) and Andy Regenberg (17) led Saugus. Jamil Austin had 19 
points and Rob Caulfield added 18 points for Canyon (8-14, 3-7). 
</P>
