<P>
2 KILLED IN CRASH OF RESCUE COPTER IN FRANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHAMBERY, France 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A British tourist injured in a skiing accident was killed when a rescue 
helicopter taking him to the hospital crashed, police said Friday. Also killed 
was the pilot, Dr. Roland Freyssinet, 68, founder of the French Air Rescue 
service. 
</P>
<P>
The helicopter was believed to have hit electric wires as it took off, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Freyssinet, who flew Spitfires for the British Royal Air Force during World War 
II, was well-known in French aviation circles. 
</P>
