<HEADLINE>
<P>
.. . PHOENIX HOUSE . . . 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am supporting the proposed Phoenix House/Nancy Reagan Center to be located in 
Lake View Terrace on the site of the former Pacoima Memorial Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
The long-term residential care offered there will be one of the few resources 
available in the San Fernando Valley for the rehabilitation of teens. I believe 
the outcry by neighbors should be considered and compromises be made to satisfy 
some of their demands. However, their objection to the treatment center should 
not be the determining factor for the zoning commission to deny Phoenix House 
the permits necessary to operate in Lake View Terrace. 
</P>
<P>
Many young adults die from drug overdoses or commit suicide from depression 
brought on by the use of drugs. The Valley needs more treatment facilities for 
these young people so they may reclaim their lives. 
</P>
<P>
MELODY SULLIVAN 
</P>
<P>
Van Nuys 
</P>
</TEXT>
