<P>
MOTORCYCLIST KILLED IN SEPULVEDA ACCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Amotorcyclist who rode into oncoming traffic on a curve in Sepulveda was struck 
by a car and killed, Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
Kevin Bolger, 24, of Northridge was fatally injured about 12:40 a.m. Friday 
when his motorcycle struck a car driven by Syed Mohammed Ali, 24, of Panorama 
City on Roscoe Boulevard near Hayvenhurst Avenue, police said. 
</P>
