<TEXT>
<P>
A Riverside real estate agent has been identified as the victim of a fatal car 
accident on Coast Highway near Laguna Beach, authorities said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
CHP Officer Mark Mudrick said Glenn C. Calvert, 64, was killed when a man 
driving north on Coast Highway about 2 miles south of Cameo Shores lost control 
of his Corvette, spun into the southbound lanes and smashed into Calvert's 
Mercury Cougar. 
</P>
<P>
Calvert was pronounced dead on arrival at Hoag Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
Walid M. Albinali, 22, of Irvine, the driver of the Corvette, remained 
hospitalized Friday with a chest injury and facial cuts. Mudrick said that the 
accident, which occurred about 1:10 p.m., was caused by the weather and that 
Albinali was not cited. Police are still investigating the accident, Mudrick 
said. Two other vehicles were involved in the accident, but neither driver was 
hurt. 
