<P>
MAZDA TO ADD 80 CAR DEALERSHIPS IN U.S. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mazda Motor Corp. said it will increase the number of its U.S. car dealers to 
900 from the current 820 by the end of 1989. 
</P>
<P>
The company will also raise the ratio of sole dealers in the United States to 
50% from about 30%, a company spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The increase and strengthening of the sales network in the U.S. comes on the 
heels of the introduction of the MX-5 and four-door sedan Capella model cars, 
the spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Mazda will export MX-5 model cars from Japan, but the Capella will be produced 
by Mazda's wholly owned U.S. subsidiary. 
</P>
